From: SeongJae Park <sj@kernel.org>
Date: Fri, 20 Feb 2026 18:01:00 -0800
Subject: [PATCH] ==== damon pause_resume ====

mm/damon: let DAMON be paused and resumed

The execution of DAMON can only be started and stopped.  Letting it be
paused and resumed can be beneficial in multiple use cases.

Tests of DAMON is one such use cases.  DAMON selftest is using drgn to
dump the internal DAMON status.  The status is investigated if it is
same to what the test code expected.  Because DAMON keeps running and
modifying its internal status, there is a chance of data race that can
cause wrong test results.

Investigation of DAMON is another use case.  When an investigation of
DAMON is needed, it is common to stop DAMON, coleecting clues for the
investigation, and restart DAMON.  It is not very useful since many of
DAMON internal clues are gone when DAMON is stopped.  Also, DAMON's
monitoring results are improved over time due to its adaptive regions
adjustment mechanism and the 'age' counters.  DAMON that restarted after
the investigation should start over from the not yet ripen monitoring
results.  This can espeically be problematic on production environment.

Monitoring of workloads that have different phases is another use case.
For example, in Android, applications are known to have very different
access pattern and behavior when they are running on the foreground and
the background.  It can therefore useful to separately monitor the
access pattern of apps while they are on the foreground and on the
background.  Having two DAMON threads per application that paused and
resumed for the apps foreground/background switches can be used for the
purpose.

Let such control be available.  Introduce a new DAMON context parameter,
namely 'pause'.  API callers can update it while the context is running,
using the online parameters update functions (damon_commit_ctx() and
damon_call()).  Once it is set, kdamond_fn() main loop will do only
limited works while sleeping sampling intervals per the work.  The
limited works include handling of the online prameters update.  Hence
users can still update the 'pause' parameter.  Once it is unset,
kdamond_fn() main loop will do the all works again.  Under the paused
state, it also does stop condition checks and handling of it.  Further
extend DAMON sysfs interface for user-space control of the feature.
Also, update existing tests to test and use the feature.

Patch 1 introduces the new parameter to core API.  Patch 2 extend DAMON
sysfs interface for the new parameter.  Patches 3-5 update design, usage
and ABI documents for the new sysfs file, respectively.  Following five
patches are for tests.  Patch 6 implement new kunit test for the pause
parameter online commitment.  Patches 7 and 8 extend DAMON selftest
helpers to support the new feature.  Patch 9 extend selftest to test the
feature.  Finally, patch 10 updates existing selftest to be safe from
the race condition using the pause/resume feature.

